  "prompt": "How do I remove another Google account from my Android?",
  "response": "Here's how to remove a Google account from an Android device:\n\n1. Open your device's \"Settings\" app\n\n2. Scroll down and tap on \"Accounts\" or \"Users & Accounts\"\n\n3. Select the Google account you want to remove\n\n4. Tap the three-dot menu or \"Remove account\"\n\n5. Confirm by tapping \"Remove account\" again\n\nThe exact steps might vary slightly depending on your Android device's make and model, but these general instructions should work for most Android phones.\n\nNote: Removing the account will delete all associated data from that account on your device, like email, contacts, and app data synced with that account.",
